AGI -&nbsp; They had organized a real supply chain that, beginning with the transport of drugs>, ran then along the managers of the delivery, of the detention, until the sale 'to detail' of the doses destined to the consumers that, on the occasion of the football competitions played at the Olympic Stadium, attend the South Curva of the plant.
In the morning of today, at the outcome of an investigation conducted by the state police and coordinated by the Anti-Mafia District Direction of the Prosecution of Rome, the Digos of the Questura has notified the Decree of Interrogation Fixation (cd "previous interrogation"), arranged by the gip, to three ultra' of the "Gruppo Quadraro">, sodalizio occupying the central part of the second ring of the Curva. At the same time and as part of the same investigation, the Digos of Rome, on the delegation of the Dda, > performed a local and personal search for the three recipients of the preventive interrogation and three other members of the above-mentioned ultra-sublititle of which a minor.
The investigations are held responsible because, within the group of the Romanist typhorist called "Gruppo Quadraro", they had been associated with each other and with a minor in order to commit more delicacies among those previewed from article 73 D.P.R. 309/90 of purchase, transport, commerce, sale, sale and illicit detention of cocaine, regularly sold on the occasion of the meetings football > They are also held responsible for the "end" offence of the sale of drugs, > as, in competition between them and with other subjects, illegally carried out numerous cessions of cocaine on the occasion of the home football matches played by Rome at the baths of the South Curva of the Olympic Stadium until May 2024. The investigations involved numerous football matches played by the Giallorossi team from January 2024.&nbsp;

